title: Print, 1730–1809
inscribed:
Imprinted at center: 2 suitte de culs se lampes et fleurons/Inventes ed Dessines Par M. Bachelier P. du Roy/Tiree de la grande Edition in-f des Fables dela Fontaine/Et Graves par PP Choffard/Avec Privilege du Roy

Imprinted at lower left: Bachelier inv.
Imprinted at lower right: PP Choffard, Sculp.
Imprinted at lower left: 7
Imprinted lower center: A Paris chez la v.Chereau rue s. Jacques aux 2 Pilliers d'Or.
Lower right hand corner: b
Inscribed in graphite below plate, lower right: 7
provenance: From the Collection of Léon Decloux
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: Title plate depicting a honey bee house and including flowers, a mask, a staff with wings, and various fruits
